1
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:35,953
BEYOND THE BAR

2
00:00:39,665 --> 00:00:42,417
<i>In this world, there are women</i>
<i>who make the impossible possible</i>

3
00:00:42,501 --> 00:00:44,253
<i>just like Wonder Woman.</i>

4
00:00:47,464 --> 00:00:49,174
<i>Some of these women excel in their careers</i>

5
00:00:49,258 --> 00:00:53,470
<i>and maintain a happy family</i>
<i>at the same time</i>

6
00:00:53,554 --> 00:00:55,931
<i>by being loving wives</i>

7
00:00:56,014 --> 00:00:58,433
<i>and supportive mothers.</i>

8
00:00:58,517 --> 00:01:01,103
It's all because of you!
How dare you run that mouth!

9
00:01:01,186 --> 00:01:05,357
<i>Others rise above every hardship they face</i>

10
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:08,277
<i>- in their own ways.</i>
- The principle that jointly earned assets…

11
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:12,281
We have with us
Professor Choi Eun-hee from SNU Law

12
00:01:12,364 --> 00:01:15,826
to discuss the recent controversy
over cryptocurrency regulation.

13
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:17,119
Thank you for making time.

14
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:18,203
NEWS ANCHOR HAN SEOL-YEON

15
00:01:18,287 --> 00:01:19,997
<i>Thank you for having me.</i>

16
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:21,915
<i>The recent announcement by the government…</i>

17
00:01:21,999 --> 00:01:24,001
Seol-a! Hyo-min! Come here! Hurry!

18
00:01:24,084 --> 00:01:24,960
What is it?

19
00:01:25,043 --> 00:01:27,129
Your mom and Seol-a's sister
are on TV together!

20
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:28,422
They are!

21
00:01:28,964 --> 00:01:32,509
Seol-yeon is always on TV
since she's the lead anchor of JTBS…

22
00:01:32,593 --> 00:01:33,635
PROFESSOR CHOI EUN-HEE

23
00:01:33,719 --> 00:01:37,180
…but even Ms. Choi's been
showing up on the news a lot lately.

24
00:01:37,264 --> 00:01:38,724
Is she getting into politics?

25
00:01:39,391 --> 00:01:43,061
With Ms. Choi getting busier,
who's going to be our domestic fairy now?

26
00:01:44,146 --> 00:01:45,939
She won't come here for a while.

27
00:01:46,023 --> 00:01:47,566
- Why not?
- Why not?

28
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:50,110
Is it because she threw away your plate?

29
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:51,695
Did you confront her about it?

30
00:01:53,405 --> 00:01:54,281
What?

31
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:58,285
Seol-yeon looks especially radiant today.

32
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:00,829
My idol, Seol-yeon.

33
00:02:00,912 --> 00:02:03,332
Ji-eun's such a Seol-yeon fangirl.

34
00:02:03,415 --> 00:02:04,750
She just looks good on camera.

35
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:10,255
<i>And others stand tall</i>
<i>in a league of their own,</i>

36
00:02:10,339 --> 00:02:12,007
<i>recognized by all.</i>

37
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:17,929
WONDER WOMAN

38
00:02:18,013 --> 00:02:20,474
- Please continue.
- Yes.

39
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:23,268
This preparatory brief,
written by Mr. Yoon Seok-hoon himself,

40
00:02:23,352 --> 00:02:27,481
includes classified material
that could severely harm MGC's case.

41
00:02:27,564 --> 00:02:28,899
With this material,

42
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:31,276
Mr. Yoon is almost certain
to win the case.

43
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:34,237
But where on earth did Mr. Yoon

44
00:02:34,863 --> 00:02:36,823
get hold of such a document?

45
00:02:37,449 --> 00:02:41,286
Ms. Seo Hye-jin is
currently representing MGC.

46
00:02:41,370 --> 00:02:45,415
So are you saying that Mr. Yoon
and Ms. Seo are in a relationship

47
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:50,295
and that she provided him

48
00:02:50,379 --> 00:02:51,463
with the document?

49
00:02:51,546 --> 00:02:53,548
Isn't that a reasonable suspicion?

50
00:02:53,632 --> 00:02:56,426
How does a document
that MGC kept under strict security

51
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:58,595
end up getting leaked?

52
00:02:58,679 --> 00:02:59,888
Perhaps

53
00:02:59,971 --> 00:03:02,599
Mr. Yoon could provide
a brief explanation regarding this.

54
00:03:05,644 --> 00:03:06,978
I won't explain myself.

55
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:13,402
Instead, I will present evidence
that proves

56
00:03:13,485 --> 00:03:15,904
Mr. Ko's claim is slanderous.

57
00:03:15,987 --> 00:03:16,863
What?

58
00:03:16,947 --> 00:03:20,742
And I request strict disciplinary action
for this malicious slander.

59
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:22,703
Okay.

60
00:03:22,786 --> 00:03:24,788
If Mr. Ko's claim is true,

61
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:27,499
Mr. Yoon will face disciplinary action.

62
00:03:27,582 --> 00:03:29,292
If it turns out to be slander,

63
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:33,004
then Mr. Ko will be
the one held accountable.

64
00:03:33,088 --> 00:03:35,465
Do either of you have any objections?

65
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:36,591
No.

66
00:03:36,675 --> 00:03:37,968
Me neither.

67
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,095
Mr. Yoon,

68
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:43,890
do you have any evidence
that this is slander?

69
00:03:43,974 --> 00:03:46,017
This is the first time I've come across

70
00:03:46,101 --> 00:03:47,477
the brief displayed on the screen.

71
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:51,606
And it's also the first time seeing
information unfavorable to MGC Securities.

72
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:53,483
That's nonsense.

73
00:03:53,567 --> 00:03:57,028
Then how was this document
submitted to the court?

74
00:03:57,112 --> 00:03:59,614
It was never submitted to the court.

75
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,324
What in the world…

76
00:04:04,536 --> 00:04:05,787
<i>Are you sure</i>

77
00:04:05,871 --> 00:04:08,248
<i>that stolen document</i>
<i>was actually submitted to the court?</i>

78
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:11,042
Feel free to verify it whenever you like.

79
00:04:14,463 --> 00:04:16,882
What's going on?

80
00:04:17,883 --> 00:04:19,259
Then

81
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:21,344
who wrote that document?

82
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:24,681
That should be fairly simple to check.

83
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:27,058
Since last year, every file has been

84
00:04:27,142 --> 00:04:30,353
assigned a unique ID
as part of the enhanced security system.

85
00:04:30,437 --> 00:04:31,438
Exactly.

86
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:33,607
There's a code
at the bottom of the document.

87
00:04:34,232 --> 00:04:35,692
I didn't know about that.

88
00:04:37,235 --> 00:04:41,239
If you trace that number,
you'll find out who wrote it.

89
00:04:44,159 --> 00:04:45,118
Come here.

90
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:46,745
Get over here.

91
00:04:49,206 --> 00:04:54,252
Who dares interrupt
the great one's gaming session?

92
00:04:57,756 --> 00:04:59,216
Hello, Kang Min-jun speaking.

93
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:02,928
Yes.

94
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:24,324
Mr. Kang Min-jun,

95
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:27,160
did you write this document?

96
00:05:27,244 --> 00:05:29,412
I'm not sure if I'm following you.

97
00:05:29,496 --> 00:05:31,998
I asked if you drafted this brief.

98
00:05:38,964 --> 00:05:40,131
No,

99
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:41,466
I've never seen this document.

100
00:05:41,550 --> 00:05:43,885
Every document has a unique ID,

101
00:05:43,969 --> 00:05:46,263
and tracking that number

102
00:05:46,972 --> 00:05:50,183
revealed that this one
was written and printed by you.

103
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:52,644
And you're saying
you know nothing about this?

104
00:06:01,278 --> 00:06:02,487
Yes?

105
00:06:05,907 --> 00:06:06,908
Okay.

106
00:06:09,327 --> 00:06:11,663
The IT team has just verified

107
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:13,748
that a copy of the document

108
00:06:13,832 --> 00:06:16,543
with the same number is stored

109
00:06:16,626 --> 00:06:17,669
on your computer, Mr. Kang.

110
00:06:18,712 --> 00:06:21,006
Are you still going to deny it?

111
00:06:25,594 --> 00:06:26,511
Moron.

112
00:06:26,595 --> 00:06:28,555
You get out, moron.

113
00:06:31,892 --> 00:06:33,393
- Jeez.
- Min-jun.

114
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:34,394
What now?

115
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:36,396
I'm in trouble. My computer crashed again.

116
00:06:36,479 --> 00:06:38,023
Again? Why?

117
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:40,442
I don't know. I need to send this
right now. I'm screwed.

118
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:42,360
It's not my problem. Ask someone else.

119
00:06:42,444 --> 00:06:43,695
Everyone's swamped with work.

120
00:06:43,778 --> 00:06:44,654
I can't!

121
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:46,406
Jeez.

122
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:49,326
How can I finish my work
and your construction payment draft

123
00:06:49,409 --> 00:06:51,369
if you won't let me use your computer?

124
00:06:52,579 --> 00:06:54,623
- Really?
- Hell yeah.

125
00:06:54,706 --> 00:06:55,707
So move.

126
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:57,876
- You'll do it for me?
- Of course.

127
00:06:57,959 --> 00:06:59,252
Don't mess with my game, though.

128
00:06:59,336 --> 00:07:00,295
Never.

129
00:07:00,378 --> 00:07:02,339
When did you level up like this?

130
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:05,383
I'll just have some coffee, then.

131
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:09,137
What a mess.

132
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:16,061
RETURN OF INVESTMENT FUNDS

133
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:20,106
EVIDENTIARY METHOD

134
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:32,869
Ms. Kim,

135
00:07:32,953 --> 00:07:35,789
this is TS Insurance's brief
against MGC Securities.

136
00:07:35,872 --> 00:07:37,666
- Please submit it to the court.
- Okay.

137
00:07:37,749 --> 00:07:38,875
Make sure it's done securely.

138
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:40,168
- Sure.
- Thank you.

139
00:07:54,265 --> 00:07:55,433
<i>This is Lee Jin-woo.</i>

140
00:07:55,517 --> 00:07:56,768
<i>Can you come to my office?</i>

141
00:07:56,851 --> 00:07:57,727
Sure.

142
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:13,618
RETURN OF INVESTMENT FUNDS

143
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:17,247
That was silly of me.

144
00:08:18,707 --> 00:08:20,417
I gave you the wrong flash drive.

145
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:23,253
I'll email you the brief
to be submitted to the court.

146
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:25,296
- Can I have my flash drive back?
- Okay.

147
00:08:25,380 --> 00:08:26,631
I'm so sorry.

148
00:08:32,012 --> 00:08:33,263
Since you can't answer,

149
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:37,100
let me ask Mr. Ko Tae-seop.

150
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:40,437
Where did you get that document?

151
00:08:44,024 --> 00:08:46,526
What do you mean?
Where would he get it from?

152
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:48,653
Mr. Kang Min-jun gave it to me,

153
00:08:48,737 --> 00:08:50,196
and I reported it to Mr. Ko

154
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:53,783
since it seemed like a serious matter.

155
00:08:57,328 --> 00:08:58,455
Mr. Kang Min-jun.

156
00:08:58,538 --> 00:08:59,414
Yes?

157
00:09:00,165 --> 00:09:01,082
Answer me.

158
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:04,711
Right.

159
00:09:08,298 --> 00:09:10,133
Could I have a little time?

160
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:11,217
Okay.

161
00:09:11,843 --> 00:09:13,887
I understand it's hard to answer,

162
00:09:13,970 --> 00:09:16,014
given the nature of the situation.

163
00:09:18,016 --> 00:09:21,436
If you don't mind, I'd like to give him
a day to think about it.

164
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:22,437
Well,

165
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:25,857
if it's okay with you,
then it's fine by me.

166
00:09:26,608 --> 00:09:27,484
Okay.

167
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:30,403
Even if Mr. Yoon's claim is true…

168
00:09:31,154 --> 00:09:32,572
Even if it's true,

169
00:09:32,655 --> 00:09:35,200
isn't it inappropriate
to bring a female attorney,

170
00:09:35,283 --> 00:09:38,495
especially one representing
the opposing party on a serious case,

171
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:40,872
to your own home

172
00:09:40,955 --> 00:09:42,582
at such a late hour?

173
00:09:44,793 --> 00:09:46,252
That?

174
00:09:46,336 --> 00:09:48,463
The reason why Ms. Seo Hye-jin came to me

175
00:09:48,546 --> 00:09:51,091
was to report workplace harassment.

176
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:52,801
And the person involved

177
00:09:53,802 --> 00:09:55,011
was Hong Do-yun.

178
00:09:56,596 --> 00:09:57,514
What?

179
00:10:04,938 --> 00:10:06,147
Mr. Yoon,

180
00:10:07,565 --> 00:10:09,400
please help me.

181
00:10:14,781 --> 00:10:15,990
At first,

182
00:10:16,699 --> 00:10:19,619
I thought he was scolding me
because I wasn't doing a good job.

183
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:21,996
Why do you make me repeat myself?

184
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:26,376
- I'm sorry.
- It's like we're collecting strays now.

185
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:31,047
<i>That's why I worked even harder.</i>

186
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:37,053
An elementary school kid
could do better than you.

187
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:38,972
I'm sorry.

188
00:10:40,807 --> 00:10:43,059
- Get ready for our team dinner.
- Yes, sir.

189
00:10:43,935 --> 00:10:45,395
- Hey.
- Yes, Mr. Hong.

190
00:10:45,937 --> 00:10:48,857
This is a bit urgent.
I need to send it by tomorrow.

191
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:51,192
You'll have to miss the dinner.

192
00:10:54,529 --> 00:10:55,488
It's fine.

193
00:10:55,572 --> 00:10:56,447
I'm sorry.

194
00:10:56,531 --> 00:10:58,158
- Let's go.
- Okay.

195
00:11:20,096 --> 00:11:22,682
PLEASE REFER TO THE ABOVE INFORMATION
FOR YOUR WORK

196
00:11:27,896 --> 00:11:30,565
<i>It was a solid brief,</i>
<i>with nothing to criticize.</i>

197
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:33,818
MR. HONG DO-YUN

198
00:11:34,611 --> 00:11:36,779
What's with this line spacing? Gosh.

199
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:39,741
How can you not even get this right?

200
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:41,326
It's all messy.

201
00:11:42,744 --> 00:11:44,078
Seriously?

202
00:11:45,163 --> 00:11:46,873
Is this how you get things done?

203
00:11:49,459 --> 00:11:51,127
- I'm sorry.
- Say it louder!

204
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:52,587
I'm sorry.

205
00:11:53,504 --> 00:11:55,048
<i>That's when I realized</i>

206
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:58,509
<i>it was harassment</i>
<i>just for the sake of harassment.</i>

207
00:11:58,593 --> 00:12:01,304
It was just too hard to endure.
I thought about reporting it,

208
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:03,348
but he holds so much power

209
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:05,350
that I had no idea how it might backfire.

210
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:09,103
I thought it could ruin my reputation
and make it harder to find a new job.

211
00:12:09,729 --> 00:12:12,732
<i>So I chose to leave</i>
<i>and began searching for a new job.</i>

212
00:12:14,192 --> 00:12:15,401
Ms. Seo.

213
00:12:16,986 --> 00:12:19,405
- Yes.
- Are you free this evening?

214
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:24,244
- Yes, I'm free.
- Good.

215
00:12:24,327 --> 00:12:26,663
I'm having dinner
with an important client tonight.

216
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:28,206
Would you like to join me?

217
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:31,542
Sure, Mr. Ko.

218
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:33,378
See you later, then.

219
00:12:42,053 --> 00:12:43,554
What a great evening.

220
00:12:43,638 --> 00:12:44,764
Thank you.

221
00:12:50,103 --> 00:12:52,814
- Please help yourself.
- Let me pour you a glass.

222
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:54,065
What an honor.

223
00:12:58,486 --> 00:13:00,363
<i>Whenever I joined him on those dinners…</i>

224
00:13:00,446 --> 00:13:01,781
- Thank you.
- Bye.

225
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:03,992
<i>…the harassment would stop for a while.</i>

226
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:13,209
Honestly,

227
00:13:13,293 --> 00:13:17,213
I never thought
you could be the life of the party.

228
00:13:17,297 --> 00:13:19,382
I didn't know you had it in you.

229
00:13:20,049 --> 00:13:20,925
Thank you.

230
00:13:21,009 --> 00:13:23,428
Now that I see it,
you have a lovely smile.

231
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:30,351
I shouldn't say things like that nowadays.

232
00:13:30,852 --> 00:13:31,769
It's fine.

233
00:13:31,853 --> 00:13:33,062
<i>I just…</i>

234
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:34,063
Is it?

235
00:13:34,147 --> 00:13:37,066
<i>I just thought of it</i>
<i>as having a fancy meal</i>

236
00:13:37,734 --> 00:13:39,736
<i>and went along once or twice a week.</i>

237
00:13:41,029 --> 00:13:42,655
Were you pressured
to entertain guests or--

238
00:13:42,739 --> 00:13:43,823
No.

239
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:46,284
Not at first.

240
00:13:47,493 --> 00:13:50,330
Most of the dinners
were formal business occasions,

241
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:51,664
but one time,

242
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:54,751
a client crossed the line,

243
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:57,295
<i>so I just walked out.</i>

244
00:13:58,421 --> 00:13:59,297
Hey.

245
00:14:01,549 --> 00:14:04,469
Do you think I became a lawyer
to be treated like this?

246
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:05,470
I know.

247
00:14:05,970 --> 00:14:07,263
Of course.

248
00:14:07,347 --> 00:14:08,598
But that guy in there,

249
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:11,184
he went to law school
but never passed the bar

250
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,269
and makes ends meet working as a broker.

251
00:14:13,895 --> 00:14:15,146
He has an inferiority complex.

252
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:17,023
That's why he acts like that
toward any lawyer,

253
00:14:17,106 --> 00:14:18,608
man or woman.

254
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:20,276
It's not just you.

255
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:22,236
Do you think that justifies his actions?

256
00:14:24,739 --> 00:14:27,116
You're cute when you're worked up.

257
00:14:28,409 --> 00:14:29,744
Come on now. Don't be mad.

258
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:31,454
I'll make sure to tell him off.

259
00:14:32,205 --> 00:14:33,456
<i>When he said that,</i>

260
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:36,626
<i>I felt a bit strange.</i>

261
00:14:38,461 --> 00:14:40,463
<i>That's when he started being nice to me.</i>

262
00:14:41,756 --> 00:14:44,634
<i>A few more dinner gatherings</i>
<i>followed after that.</i>

263
00:14:51,599 --> 00:14:52,517
It's okay.

264
00:14:53,851 --> 00:14:55,186
Say what you want to say.

265
00:14:58,856 --> 00:15:00,108
I ended up…

266
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:03,945
sleeping with him.

267
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:07,156
I feel so ashamed

268
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:09,909
that I fell for his schemes,

269
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:12,161
but I didn't see it back then.

270
00:15:12,245 --> 00:15:16,290
After that, he started inviting me
to dinner more openly and frequently.

271
00:15:16,374 --> 00:15:18,084
He said his success
would benefit me as well.

272
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:20,628
<i>I tried to walk away every time, but…</i>

273
00:15:21,504 --> 00:15:23,172
Instead of giving me actual work,

274
00:15:23,714 --> 00:15:25,716
why do you keep insisting
on dinner meetings?

275
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,385
Dinner meetings are part of work too.

276
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:29,053
Just log it on your time sheet.

277
00:15:29,137 --> 00:15:31,764
No, from now on,
I won't be joining you for dinner.

278
00:15:31,848 --> 00:15:33,307
If you keep pressuring me,

279
00:15:34,058 --> 00:15:36,310
I will report it as workplace harassment.

280
00:15:41,566 --> 00:15:42,650
Workplace harassment?

281
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:45,695
Hey,

282
00:15:45,778 --> 00:15:48,865
who would believe a woman
who messed around with a married man?

283
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:50,950
What?

284
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:53,369
If you report me,
do you think I'll stay quiet?

285
00:15:53,453 --> 00:15:55,955
All I have to say
is that we're in a relationship

286
00:15:56,038 --> 00:15:58,207
and you joined those dinners on your own.

287
00:15:58,291 --> 00:16:00,293
So tell me. If that happens,
who ends up losing?

288
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:01,252
You or me?

289
00:16:01,878 --> 00:16:03,963
We both may be criticized,
but women get it worse.

290
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:05,089
Do you know why?

291
00:16:05,673 --> 00:16:08,050
People think, "Even if he's married,

292
00:16:08,134 --> 00:16:10,803
what man could resist
someone as young, smart,

293
00:16:10,887 --> 00:16:12,889
and pretty as you coming on to him?"

294
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:16,017
But you? Do you think
you could get married after that?

295
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:18,102
What utter nonsense.

296
00:16:18,769 --> 00:16:22,398
<i>He used that one encounter</i>
<i>to blackmail me.</i>

297
00:16:23,483 --> 00:16:25,318
I even thought about ending my life.

298
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:30,573
But I came to you as a last resort.

299
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:35,328
There are other female associates

300
00:16:36,746 --> 00:16:38,122
who went through the same thing.

301
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:44,253
She is my client.

302
00:16:44,754 --> 00:16:45,922
I will take care of it.

303
00:16:47,131 --> 00:16:49,133
Look at you, acting up again.

304
00:16:49,217 --> 00:16:50,927
Why are you being such a brat?

305
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:54,096
What's going on?

306
00:16:54,764 --> 00:16:57,850
It's nothing.
Just be on your way. Damn it…

307
00:17:02,647 --> 00:17:04,190
What do you think you're doing?

308
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:05,900
Jeez.

309
00:17:10,655 --> 00:17:13,074
Ko Eun-jin, Kim Su-mi.

310
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:15,785
I guess your next target is Kang Hyo-min.

311
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:20,206
Start groveling
if you don't want to be buried.

312
00:17:26,671 --> 00:17:28,297
I'll take care of it.

313
00:17:45,273 --> 00:17:48,067
Four years ago, it was carried out
in a completely organized way.

314
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:49,777
But these days, it's much…

315
00:17:52,697 --> 00:17:53,781
Ms. Kwon.

316
00:17:53,864 --> 00:17:55,032
What are you…

317
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:59,662
Tell me what's going on right now.

318
00:18:00,413 --> 00:18:01,330
It's…

319
00:18:01,831 --> 00:18:04,250
We were in the middle of a team dinner.

320
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:07,253
You were having a team dinner
at a private entertainment bar,

321
00:18:07,878 --> 00:18:09,672
and you only invited
the female associates?

322
00:18:09,755 --> 00:18:12,842
The male attorneys were…

323
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:15,177
Mr. Choi Jeong-hyeok and Mr. Kim Ho-jin

324
00:18:15,261 --> 00:18:17,263
had prior engagements,
so they couldn't join--

325
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:20,099
Mr. Choi Jeong-hyeok and Mr. Kim Ho-jin.

326
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:21,767
- Yes.
- Yes.

327
00:18:21,851 --> 00:18:25,563
Was there something urgent that kept you
from joining the team dinner today?

328
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:28,149
- No, ma'am.
- No, ma'am.

329
00:18:33,696 --> 00:18:34,697
Who are they?

330
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:40,202
Ms. Shin Eun-mi.

331
00:18:40,286 --> 00:18:41,370
Who are these people?

332
00:18:50,546 --> 00:18:52,006
I just asked who they were.

333
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:56,135
They're brokers.

334
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:08,481
You're aware that brokering legal services

335
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:11,776
through someone who's not a lawyer
is a criminal violation, aren't you?

336
00:19:12,485 --> 00:19:13,944
I am, but…

337
00:19:14,862 --> 00:19:15,863
But I…

338
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:18,199
Submit a resignation form by tomorrow.

339
00:19:18,282 --> 00:19:19,742
File a criminal complaint

340
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:23,120
and pursue all legally available
disciplinary actions.

341
00:19:23,204 --> 00:19:24,080
Yes, ma'am.

342
00:19:26,749 --> 00:19:30,002
Ms. Kwon, please give me a chance
to explain myself at the office.

343
00:19:34,590 --> 00:19:36,050
Ms. Kwon, that's…

344
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:40,930
How dare you

345
00:19:41,555 --> 00:19:43,265
treat female Yullim lawyers

346
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:45,267
like hostesses?

347
00:19:46,977 --> 00:19:47,853
You.

348
00:19:49,105 --> 00:19:52,358
Don't ever set foot in the legal field,
even if you starve to death.

349
00:19:59,907 --> 00:20:02,702
You should have given me a call.

350
00:20:04,078 --> 00:20:05,621
You crazy bastard.

351
00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:08,499
Are you serious?

352
00:20:11,001 --> 00:20:12,420
Seriously?

353
00:20:21,846 --> 00:20:22,888
Mr. Yoon.

354
00:20:25,141 --> 00:20:26,183
Are you satisfied now?

355
00:20:29,478 --> 00:20:31,522
Let's pin it all on Hong Do-yun

356
00:20:31,605 --> 00:20:33,774
and have the statement say it was him

357
00:20:33,858 --> 00:20:36,068
who made Kang Min-jun
carry out the scheme.

358
00:20:37,570 --> 00:20:38,946
Why should I?

359
00:20:39,029 --> 00:20:41,615
I'm the son of Ko Seung-cheol,
a founder of Yullim.

360
00:20:42,158 --> 00:20:44,577
You're smart enough to know
that messing with me will get ugly.

361
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:46,954
Are you asking me for a favor
or threatening me?

362
00:20:49,665 --> 00:20:51,500
I'm asking you for a favor.

363
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:53,294
Let's leave it at this for now.

364
00:20:56,464 --> 00:20:59,133
- Is this how you ask for a favor?
- Damn it, then what?

365
00:20:59,216 --> 00:21:00,301
Should I kneel or something?

366
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:06,432
The foundation of any deal
is giving and taking.

367
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:09,602
Assign Mr. Choi Hui-cheol

368
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:13,314
to DA Solutions.

369
00:21:15,357 --> 00:21:16,317
What?

370
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:19,904
The position you pushed
Ms. Kwon Na-yeon into with your scheming.

371
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:25,159
Or would you like to go there
in Mr. Choi's place?

372
00:21:28,913 --> 00:21:30,247
One more thing.

373
00:21:36,086 --> 00:21:37,713
From now on, whatever I do,

374
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:41,091
you stay quiet and do nothing.

375
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:54,855
Big news! This is insane.

376
00:21:54,939 --> 00:21:56,065
Mr. Hong Do-yun.

377
00:21:56,732 --> 00:21:58,526
- He resigned.
- What?

378
00:21:58,609 --> 00:21:59,485
That's so sudden.

379
00:21:59,568 --> 00:22:02,238
Security is packing up
Mr. Hong's things as we speak.

380
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:04,448
My goodness. What on earth…

381
00:22:04,532 --> 00:22:05,699
- Right?
- What's going on?

382
00:22:05,783 --> 00:22:08,410
But honestly,
everyone seems kind of relieved.

383
00:22:08,494 --> 00:22:09,829
I bet.

384
00:22:09,912 --> 00:22:11,455
HAN SEOL-A

385
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:16,877
Hey, Seol-a.

386
00:22:20,214 --> 00:22:21,465
Seol-yeon is?

387
00:22:22,091 --> 00:22:24,218
Which police station? I'll be right there.

388
00:22:27,137 --> 00:22:28,556
Mr. Choi Min-gu. Hey!

389
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:31,517
What are you looking at?

390
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:34,895
Answer me. Where were you
at two o'clock last Wednesday?

391
00:22:34,979 --> 00:22:37,690
So it is her!
Han Seol-yeon, the news anchor!

392
00:22:38,649 --> 00:22:40,067
- He's right.
- It's Han Seol-yeon.

393
00:22:40,150 --> 00:22:41,652
Han Seol-yeon!

394
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:42,945
Don't take pictures!

395
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:43,904
Put it down.

396
00:22:43,988 --> 00:22:45,656
- Give it to me.
- What's going on?

397
00:22:45,739 --> 00:22:48,242
Be quiet. And sit down, all of you.

398
00:22:48,826 --> 00:22:49,869
Seol-yeon!

399
00:22:56,125 --> 00:22:57,251
Seol-yeon.

400
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:01,881
- Seol-a.
- Are you okay?

401
00:23:02,756 --> 00:23:03,632
Open the door.

402
00:23:03,716 --> 00:23:04,800
I can't.

403
00:23:04,884 --> 00:23:06,385
I'm Ms. Han Seol-yeon's attorney.

404
00:23:06,468 --> 00:23:08,137
You see this?

405
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:09,763
She threw a huge fit.

406
00:23:10,806 --> 00:23:12,474
She was so strong.

407
00:23:12,558 --> 00:23:15,561
I tried to go easy on her
since she's a public figure,

408
00:23:15,644 --> 00:23:17,104
but she was uncontrollable.

409
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,316
Seol-yeon,

410
00:23:21,150 --> 00:23:22,109
what happened?

411
00:23:23,485 --> 00:23:24,695
I don't remember.

412
00:23:25,362 --> 00:23:28,407
I took the medicine prescribed
by my psychiatrist, fell asleep,

413
00:23:29,408 --> 00:23:30,868
and when I came to,

414
00:23:32,661 --> 00:23:33,621
I was here.

415
00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:35,706
What happened?

416
00:23:35,789 --> 00:23:39,460
She assaulted her husband
and was arrested on the spot.

417
00:23:40,210 --> 00:23:43,756
She'll be facing a warrant
for aggravated assault within 48 hours.

418
00:23:43,839 --> 00:23:46,258
No, wait a minute.

419
00:23:46,342 --> 00:23:47,760
That makes no sense.

420
00:23:48,260 --> 00:23:50,930
My sister has never even cursed at anyone

421
00:23:51,013 --> 00:23:52,598
or gotten into a fight.

422
00:23:53,515 --> 00:23:55,643
What do you mean, aggravated assault?

423
00:23:55,726 --> 00:23:57,394
And she targeted her husband?

424
00:23:57,478 --> 00:24:01,065
All the evidence was secured,
and she was arrested on the spot.

425
00:24:05,069 --> 00:24:06,695
Where is her husband?

426
00:24:07,446 --> 00:24:10,199
The victim is getting treated
at the hospital now,

427
00:24:10,282 --> 00:24:11,951
and things aren't looking great.

428
00:24:17,373 --> 00:24:20,250
<i>News anchor Han Seol-yeon</i>
<i>was taken into emergency custody</i>

429
00:24:20,334 --> 00:24:22,378
<i>for allegedly assaulting her husband.</i>

430
00:24:22,461 --> 00:24:23,879
<i>She was just spotted</i>

431
00:24:23,963 --> 00:24:26,548
<i>leaving the police station</i>
<i>after questioning.</i>

432
00:24:27,132 --> 00:24:30,427
<i>Ms. Han won the public's heart</i>
<i>with her bold professional presence</i>

433
00:24:30,511 --> 00:24:32,221
<i>and family-oriented nature.</i>

434
00:24:32,930 --> 00:24:36,767
<i>The pretrial detention hearing</i>
<i>to decide whether a warrant will be issued</i>

435
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:39,895
<i>is scheduled for 10:30 a.m. on Wednesday.</i>

436
00:24:40,729 --> 00:24:42,606
Unbelievable.

437
00:24:42,690 --> 00:24:44,274
So you're saying Ms. Han Seol-yeon

438
00:24:44,358 --> 00:24:46,777
is your roommate's older sister, right?

439
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:48,028
Yes.

440
00:24:48,112 --> 00:24:49,530
We're not just roommates.

441
00:24:49,613 --> 00:24:51,657
We've been like sisters
since elementary school.

442
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:53,117
My gosh.

443
00:24:53,659 --> 00:24:56,286
She doesn't seem like
the kind of person who'd hit her husband.

444
00:24:56,370 --> 00:24:58,122
She's not.

445
00:24:59,081 --> 00:25:00,416
Something feels off.

446
00:25:00,499 --> 00:25:03,377
Let's start by preparing
for the warrant review hearing.

447
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:05,379
Okay, I'm on it.

448
00:25:05,921 --> 00:25:08,007
COURT

449
00:25:08,090 --> 00:25:10,843
The defendant lives
at a permanent address.

450
00:25:10,926 --> 00:25:14,263
She has a stable job
and resides with her family.

451
00:25:14,346 --> 00:25:16,390
There's no flight risk.

452
00:25:16,473 --> 00:25:18,350
We respectfully ask the court

453
00:25:18,434 --> 00:25:20,686
to reject the motion
for a detention warrant.

454
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:22,438
Understood.

455
00:25:22,521 --> 00:25:26,400
There is insufficient evidence to justify
the need for pretrial detention.

456
00:25:26,483 --> 00:25:28,652
The request
for a detention warrant is dismissed.

457
00:25:28,736 --> 00:25:30,404
PROSECUTION

458
00:25:39,329 --> 00:25:41,165
Don't worry.

459
00:25:41,832 --> 00:25:43,584
There's a strong chance of acquittal.

460
00:25:44,209 --> 00:25:46,086
We can claim mental incapacity.

461
00:25:47,129 --> 00:25:48,464
Since she was under the influence

462
00:25:48,547 --> 00:25:51,425
of psychiatric drugs
and not in a conscious state,

463
00:25:51,508 --> 00:25:54,636
a mental incapacity defense
could result in a not-guilty verdict.

464
00:25:56,055 --> 00:25:58,140
Han Seol-a, don't you trust me?

465
00:25:58,724 --> 00:26:00,184
It's me, Kang Hyo-min.

466
00:26:01,477 --> 00:26:02,519
Yes.

467
00:26:03,395 --> 00:26:04,605
Don't worry.

468
00:26:08,525 --> 00:26:10,486
It's not easy to claim mental incapacity.

469
00:26:10,569 --> 00:26:12,654
If mental incapacity is acknowledged,

470
00:26:12,738 --> 00:26:14,823
the court is required to rule not guilty.

471
00:26:14,907 --> 00:26:17,534
That's why the court
has to be extra cautious,

472
00:26:17,618 --> 00:26:20,120
and the trial process
is likely to take longer.

473
00:26:20,204 --> 00:26:22,790
Even if she's acquitted
in the first trial,

474
00:26:22,873 --> 00:26:26,126
the trial will likely continue
if the prosecution files an appeal.

475
00:26:26,210 --> 00:26:30,089
Realistically, it's much better
to plead diminished capacity

476
00:26:30,172 --> 00:26:32,424
and aim for a suspended sentence.

477
00:26:33,050 --> 00:26:34,259
No, Mr. Yoon.

478
00:26:34,343 --> 00:26:36,345
It has to be mental incapacity.

479
00:26:36,428 --> 00:26:38,138
She's a famous news anchor.

480
00:26:38,222 --> 00:26:40,224
Unless she's acquitted, it's pointless.

481
00:26:40,307 --> 00:26:42,142
You know as well as I do

482
00:26:42,226 --> 00:26:43,227
that there's a risk.

483
00:26:44,394 --> 00:26:46,480
I know. But still,

484
00:26:48,065 --> 00:26:49,441
she has to be acquitted.

485
00:26:49,525 --> 00:26:53,737
Ms. Han Seol-yeon is family
and the pride of my lifelong friend.

486
00:26:54,363 --> 00:26:58,033
I couldn't bear to see her
get a criminal record.

487
00:26:58,117 --> 00:27:01,745
Please go for the mental incapacity plea.

488
00:27:03,872 --> 00:27:05,040
I'll think about it.

489
00:27:05,958 --> 00:27:08,752
First, we need to consult
Ms. Han's doctor.

490
00:27:21,390 --> 00:27:22,266
Hello.

491
00:27:23,684 --> 00:27:25,269
Yes, that's right.

492
00:27:26,603 --> 00:27:27,646
Is that so?

493
00:27:28,397 --> 00:27:30,232
I'll be right there.

494
00:27:31,024 --> 00:27:32,276
It won't take long.

495
00:27:33,110 --> 00:27:34,236
Yes.

496
00:27:34,319 --> 00:27:36,155
See you soon.

497
00:28:00,679 --> 00:28:02,097
Get in.

498
00:28:02,181 --> 00:28:03,557
It's okay. I'll take a cab.

499
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:05,601
Get in. I'll drop you off.

500
00:28:10,522 --> 00:28:11,440
Thanks.

501
00:28:16,403 --> 00:28:18,447
But this sure is amazing.

502
00:28:18,530 --> 00:28:21,158
I was able to reach you
a day before emigrating.

503
00:28:21,241 --> 00:28:23,368
Funny how the internet makes
things like this possible.

504
00:28:23,452 --> 00:28:24,411
Indeed.

505
00:28:28,332 --> 00:28:29,208
Here.

506
00:28:30,292 --> 00:28:31,919
It broke a long time ago,

507
00:28:32,002 --> 00:28:34,588
and I couldn't fix it
since it's discontinued.

508
00:28:34,671 --> 00:28:36,965
But it ended up being useful again.

509
00:28:37,049 --> 00:28:37,966
Right.

510
00:28:38,508 --> 00:28:40,677
I bought it for my honeymoon.

511
00:28:40,761 --> 00:28:44,014
I didn't know how to use it back then,
so I saved everything on the camera.

512
00:28:44,097 --> 00:28:45,974
I switched to external storage later on,

513
00:28:46,058 --> 00:28:48,644
but I never deleted
what was originally saved on the camera.

514
00:28:48,727 --> 00:28:49,895
I see.

515
00:28:50,437 --> 00:28:51,313
Funny, isn't it?

516
00:28:52,064 --> 00:28:54,024
It's like it was all meant to happen.

517
00:28:55,984 --> 00:28:58,445
You can't view the footage
on any other device.

518
00:28:58,528 --> 00:29:00,072
To see the videos,

519
00:29:00,822 --> 00:29:03,825
you have to get it fixed,
but I'm not sure if that's possible.

520
00:29:04,493 --> 00:29:05,744
I'll give it a shot.

